This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:

summary(cars)
##      speed           dist       
##  Min.   : 4.0   Min.   :  2.00  
##  1st Qu.:12.0   1st Qu.: 26.00  
##  Median :15.0   Median : 36.00  
##  Mean   :15.4   Mean   : 42.98  
##  3rd Qu.:19.0   3rd Qu.: 56.00  
##  Max.   :25.0   Max.   :120.00
##      speed           dist       
##  Min.   : 4.0   Min.   :  2.00  
##  1st Qu.:12.0   1st Qu.: 26.00  
##  Median :15.0   Median : 36.00  
##  Mean   :15.4   Mean   : 42.98  
##  3rd Qu.:19.0   3rd Qu.: 56.00  
##  Max.   :25.0   Max.   :120.00
summary(cars)
summary(cars)

You can also embed plots, for example:

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.

Markdown Quick Reference

R markdown is an easy-to-write plain text format for creating dynamic documents and report.See Using R Markdown to learn more.

{r,echo=TRUE,eval=FALSE,fig.height=2/8,fig.width=2/8,message=FALSE,warning=FALSE,include=FALSE,results='markup'/'asis'/'hold'/'hide',fig.align='left'/'right'/'center',}

Emphasis

*italic* _italic_  
**blod** __blod__

Demonstrate:
italic italic
blod blod

Headers

# Header 1
## Header 2
### Header 3
#### Header 4
##### Header 5
###### Header 6

Demonstrate:

Header 1

Header 2

Header 3

Header 4

Header 5
Header 6

Lists

underlist

* Item 1
* Item 2
    + Item 2a
    + Item 2b

Demonstrate:

  • Item 1
  • Item 2
    • Item 2a
    • Item 2b

Ordered List:

1. Item 1
2. Item 2
3. Item 3
    + Item 3a
    + Item 3b

Demonstrate:

  1. Item 1
  2. Item 2
  3. Item 3
    • Item 3a
    • Item 3b

Manual Line Breaks

End a line with two or more spaces:

Roses are red,  
Violets are blue.

Demonstrate:

Roses are red,
Violets are blue.

Links

Use a plain http address or add a link to a phrase:

[Using R Markdown](http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com/)

Demonstrate:

Using R Markdown

Images

Images on the web or local files in the same directory:

![alt text](http://example.com/logo.png)

![alt text](figures/img.png)

Local image:

Internet Image:

Blockquotes

A friend once said:

> It's always better to give 
> than to receive.

Demonstrate:

A friend once said:

It’s always better to give than to receive.

R Code Blocks

R code will be evaluated and printed

summary(cars$dist)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##    2.00   26.00   36.00   42.98   56.00  120.00
summary(cars$speed)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##     4.0    12.0    15.0    15.4    19.0    25.0

Inline R Code

There were `r nrow(cars)` cars studied

Demonstrate:

There were 50 cars studied

Plain Code Blocks

Plain code blocks are displayed in a fixed-width font but not evaulated

This text is displayed verbatim / preformatted

Demonstrate:

This text is displayed verbatim / preformatted

Inline Code

We defined the `add` function to 
compute the sum of two numbers.

Demonstrate:

We defined the add function to compute the sum of two numbers.

LaTeX Equations

Inline Equation

$a + b$

Demonstrate:

\(a + b\)

Display Equation

$$ a +b = c $$
<math ...> </math>          #What's the meaning ?

Demonstrate:

\[ a +b = c \]

Three or more asterisks or dashes:

******

Caching

Typographic Entities

ASCII characters are transformed into typographic HTML entities:
Straight quotes ( " and ' ) into “curly” quotes
Dashes (“--” and “---”) into en- and em-dash entities
Three consecutive dots (“...”) into an ellipsis entity
